--------------------------------------------------------------------------From S-SUWA@NRI.CO.JP Fri Aug  5 18:05:29 1994Excerpt from , S-SUWA@NRI.CO.JP in <9408030840.AA02012@postit.nri.co.jp>, 3 Aug 1994 22:21:43 -0700:For dynamic popup menus in MacApp 3, Bob Hablutzel's postings in MacApp3Tech$in 1993 (found on E.T.O. CD-ROMs) were very helpful.--------------------------------------------------------------------------From USER@JBISHOP.SLIP.NETCOM.COM Mon Aug  8 18:25:09 1994Excerpt from , USER@JBISHOP.SLIP.NETCOM.COM in <776195287.4794476@AppleLink.Apple.COM>, 6 Aug 1994 11:07:30 -0700:Ken:I've battled TPopup for 2 years...  I do what you want to do regularilynow without too much difficulty.  Stuff here is using MacApp 3.1: Some things to check:1.  When you insert an item, be sure to call SetLongValues.2.  When a menu changes, you may wish to call DoSetupMenus if a newly    added item is now the newly selected item.3.  Here's some code from a subclassed TPopup that I use - the insert short   oldMax = this->GetNumberOfItems();  // Get count of our itemsshort   currentItem = this->GetCurrentItem();  // Get the current item if (afterItem >= oldMax)   this->AppendPopupItem(itemText);else{    MenuHandle  mH = this->GetMenuHandle();   // Get our handle    InsertMenuItem(mH, itemText, afterItem); // Insert in menu via the toolbox   this->SetLongValues(currentItem, 1, (VCoordinate)(oldMax + 1),                           kDontRedraw);   // very important. MacApp stores the number of items in TPopup.fLongVal   // if you don4t do that, you can4t SetCurrentItem.    if (afterItem < currentItem)  // Inserting an item before current item   {      // Set the old item back (now 1 position deeper in menu      this->SetCurrentItem(currentItem + 1, kDontRedraw);      this->DoSetupMenus();   // Things have moved... reset the menu   } 